1 secretary of state an oath of office for the faithful discharge of official
2 duties. The election commissioner shall be a resident of the county on the
3 day such election commissioner files the oath of office.
4 (b) On and after July 1, 2025, the secretary of state shall not appoint
5 any person to the office of county election commissioner, including the
6 appointment of any person to serve the unexpired term upon a vacancy in
7 the office of county election commissioner. Upon the vacancy in the office
8 of county election commissioner in any county whether by expiration of
9 such officer's term or otherwise, all jurisdiction, powers and duties of such
10 office of county election commissioner relating to the conduct, supervision
11 and control of elections, including, but not limited to, the registration,
12 qualification, challenging and voting of qualified electors at any election
13 in any such county, shall be transferred to the county clerk of such county.
14 Upon the transfer of such jurisdiction, powers and duties, the county clerk
15 shall conduct all elections in such county in accordance with K.S.A. 2024
16 Supp. 25-126, and amendments thereto. All files, books, records, papers,
17 documents and data pertaining to elections and necessary to the proper
18 administration of elections and voter registrations under the jurisdiction
19 and control of the office of county election commissioner shall be
20 transferred and delivered to the county clerk.
21 (c) On such date as no person holds the office of county election
22 commissioner in this state, the provisions of article 34 of chapter 19 of the
23 Kansas Statutes Annotated shall have no force and effect.
24 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 19-3419 is hereby repealed.
25 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
26 publication in the statute book.

